## Install Steps

### 1 · Extract the package

```bash
tar -xzf {{ manifest.name }}-{{ manifest.version }}.skill.tar.gz
cd {{ manifest.name }}-{{ manifest.version }}
```

### 2 · Create the runtime environment

{% if manifest.runtime.type == "python" %}
```bash
python{{ manifest.runtime.python_version or "3" }} -m venv .venv
```

### 3 · Install dependencies

```bash
# Linux / macOS
.venv/bin/pip install -r requirements.txt

# Windows
.venv\Scripts\pip install -r requirements.txt
```
{% elif manifest.runtime.type == "node" %}
```bash
npm install
```
{% endif %}

### 4 · Register with Claude Code

Add the following to `~/.claude.json` under `mcpServers`:

```json
"{{ manifest.name }}": {
  "type": "{{ manifest.mcp.transport }}",
  "command": "/ABSOLUTE/PATH/.venv/bin/python",
  "args": ["/ABSOLUTE/PATH/{{ manifest.mcp.entrypoint }}"]
}
```

### 5 · Register with Codex

Add the following to `~/.codex/config.toml` under `[mcp_servers]`:

```toml
[mcp_servers.{{ manifest.name }}]
command = "/ABSOLUTE/PATH/.venv/bin/python"
args    = ["/ABSOLUTE/PATH/{{ manifest.mcp.entrypoint }}"]
```

---

## Automated Setup

If you have `skill-mcp-protocol` installed, an AI agent (Claude Code or Codex)
can perform these steps automatically by reading `agent-setup.json` in this package.

```
smcp import ./{{ manifest.name }}-{{ manifest.version }}.skill.tar.gz
```

---

## Uninstall

```bash
smcp remove {{ manifest.name }}
# or manually:
rm -rf .venv   # removes env only
```
